SIMPLE: snaky
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Snaky
<hw>Snak"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining to a snake or snakes; resembling a snake; serpentine;
winding.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The red light playing upon its gilt and carving gave it an
appearance of <qex>snaky</qex> life.</q> <rj><qau>L.
Wallace.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Sly; cunning; insinuating; deceitful.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So to the coast of Jordan he directs⟦br⟧
His easy steps, girded with <qex>snaky</qex> wiles.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Covered with serpents; having serpents; <as>as, a
<ex>snaky</ex> rod or wand</as>.</def> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That <qex>snaky</qex>-headed, Gorgon shield.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snap</ent>⟦br⟧
